WEBVTT

00:02.503 --> 00:05.139
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:21.489 --> 00:25.559
♪♪

00:26.627 --> 00:28.028
[ Doorbell rings ]

00:35.269 --> 00:37.271
Did anyone
order anything?
Together: Nah.

00:37.305 --> 00:39.039
This was the credit-card
company's answer

00:39.073 --> 00:40.774
when I asked if I can
order things online.

00:40.808 --> 00:42.710
[ Laughter through telephone ]

00:42.743 --> 00:43.944
It's been like that
for three days.

00:43.977 --> 00:45.446
I think they're working
in shifts.

00:45.479 --> 00:48.682
Well, it was delivered
to our door, so...

00:48.716 --> 00:49.717
[ Sloop! ]

00:49.750 --> 00:51.018
Uh -- uh...

00:51.051 --> 00:52.686
Opening other people's mail
is a crime!

00:52.720 --> 00:54.855
Oh, why is there always a law
against everything I want to do?

00:54.888 --> 00:56.424
Because the last thing
you wanted to do

00:56.457 --> 00:58.359
was to move into the supermarket
so you could eat for free.

00:58.392 --> 01:00.261
Uh, if the food
enters your body and exits it

01:00.294 --> 01:02.596
while still in the supermarket,
it's technically not stealing.

01:02.630 --> 01:04.098
-Hmm.
-Hmm.

01:04.132 --> 01:06.100
Come on! Am I the only one
who wants to open the box?

01:06.134 --> 01:08.702
Opening other people's mail
is like staring at the sun --

01:08.736 --> 01:10.738
the more people tell you
you shouldn't do it,

01:10.771 --> 01:12.640
the more you just gotta.

01:12.673 --> 01:14.074
Mom: Richard,
we're over here.

01:14.108 --> 01:15.276
Oh, yeah, sorry.

01:15.309 --> 01:17.478
Now, kids, there's plenty
of fun things we could do

01:17.511 --> 01:18.846
to take our mind off
opening the box.

01:18.879 --> 01:19.947
Just think
outside the box.

01:19.980 --> 01:21.515
Play some music
on the boom box,

01:21.549 --> 01:22.883
maybe go watch
a boxing match,

01:22.916 --> 01:24.752
or just open the box,
the box -- open the box!

01:24.785 --> 01:26.420
[ Panting ]

01:26.454 --> 01:28.021
Wait.
I think know what it is.

01:28.055 --> 01:29.957
It's a teleportation gun.

01:29.990 --> 01:31.225
How could you possibly know

01:31.259 --> 01:32.960
what a fictional object
sounds like?

01:32.993 --> 01:35.396
Uh, what does
a laser sword sound like?

01:35.429 --> 01:36.430
Together: Pshew!

01:36.464 --> 01:38.999
Wah-wah.
Pshew!

01:39.032 --> 01:39.833
Hwoosh!

01:39.867 --> 01:41.202
Case closed.
Box open.

01:41.235 --> 01:43.271
We're not opening it.
Oh, come on.

01:43.304 --> 01:46.674
Think about how this
could benefit society
and enrich our lives...

01:46.707 --> 01:48.242
[ "Lives" echoing ]

01:48.276 --> 01:51.512
Gumball, I told you
to take out the garbage.

01:51.545 --> 01:54.182
[ Beep, laser firing ]

01:54.215 --> 01:55.983
[ Grunts, sighs ]

01:56.016 --> 01:58.719
I'm not sure
I'm comfortable with this.

01:58.752 --> 02:00.254
Speak for yourself.

02:01.622 --> 02:03.391
[ Lasers firing ]

02:03.424 --> 02:04.425
Hi, Mom.

02:04.458 --> 02:05.726
What are you doing?

02:05.759 --> 02:07.661
I just found a way
to avoid walking.

02:07.695 --> 02:09.263
Are you sure
that thing is safe?

02:09.297 --> 02:11.199
I think so.
What makes you say that?

02:11.232 --> 02:14.668
Uh, probably that weird thing
on your nose.

02:16.069 --> 02:18.906
It seems teleportation is
dangerously affecting your DNA.

02:18.939 --> 02:21.275
So you're saying
I'm getting superpowers?

02:21.309 --> 02:22.276
No.

02:22.310 --> 02:23.677
That's a rather specific
interpretation

02:23.711 --> 02:24.878
of what I just said.

02:24.912 --> 02:27.080
But you're not saying
that I won't?

02:27.114 --> 02:28.182
Indeed.

02:28.216 --> 02:30.484
But I would say
there is a 99.9% chance

02:30.518 --> 02:32.119
you will turn into
a cyst-like pile of flesh

02:32.152 --> 02:33.821
with tongues where
there shouldn't be tongues.

02:33.854 --> 02:35.723
Oh. Uh, right.

02:35.756 --> 02:37.258
I -- I understand.

02:37.291 --> 02:38.359
Good.
Finally.

02:38.392 --> 02:41.762
So you're saying
there's a 0.01% chance

02:41.795 --> 02:43.163
that I could get
superpowers?!

02:43.197 --> 02:45.032
[ Laser fires ]
No, no, no, no!

02:45.899 --> 02:48.068
Hey, dude -- whoa!

02:48.101 --> 02:50.238
Looks like you've been
teleporting...

02:50.271 --> 02:51.805
a lot.

02:51.839 --> 02:53.874
[ Squish! ]
Whoa.
What's that?!

02:53.907 --> 02:55.943
I've been trying
to get superpowers.

02:55.976 --> 02:58.546
I wanted to fly, so I took
a bird through the portal.

02:58.579 --> 03:00.080
But instead,
now I can lay eggs.

03:00.113 --> 03:01.715
Then I tried to get
invisibility,

03:01.749 --> 03:03.116
so I took
a chameleon through.

03:03.150 --> 03:05.486
[ Belches ] And now
I can lay chameleon eggs.

03:05.519 --> 03:07.988
[ Belches ] And then
I tried to get super jump,

03:08.021 --> 03:09.790
so I took a frog through,
and --

03:09.823 --> 03:10.991
Now you can lay...

03:11.024 --> 03:12.360
[ Belches ]
[ Squish! ]

03:12.393 --> 03:15.429
Uh, yeah. So, uh,
I decided to take something

03:15.463 --> 03:16.830
that couldn't lay eggs,

03:16.864 --> 03:18.899
and ta-da!
[ Belches ]

03:18.932 --> 03:20.901
Ah, a laser pointer.
Did it work?

03:20.934 --> 03:22.336
[ Belches ]
Sure did.

03:22.370 --> 03:23.537
Check this out.

03:23.571 --> 03:24.705
Laser vision!

03:24.738 --> 03:26.139
Oh, great.

03:26.173 --> 03:28.141
Now I can see exactly where
you're looking.

03:28.175 --> 03:30.344
But maybe you should
focus some of your efforts

03:30.378 --> 03:32.246
on the aesthetic side
of superheroes.

03:32.280 --> 03:35.549
You know, maybe look
a little less like...

03:35.583 --> 03:37.518
[ Groans ]
...that.

03:37.551 --> 03:38.919
[ Belches ]
You're right.

03:38.952 --> 03:41.755
I need to merge with something
that looks super cool.

03:46.594 --> 03:47.861
[ Beep ]
Okay, wait a minute.

03:47.895 --> 03:49.597
I'm just gonna say
what we're all thinking...

03:49.630 --> 03:51.231
Please do.

03:51.265 --> 03:53.301
Are you gonna finish
that fictional food
that's on your plate?

03:53.334 --> 03:54.535
What?!
No!

03:54.568 --> 03:56.537
Why did you choose to merge
with a cockroach?

03:56.570 --> 03:58.038
Just imagine
what I could do

03:58.071 --> 04:00.240
with the powers of
a nuclear-resistant parasite!

04:00.274 --> 04:01.709
Repel girls
even more?

04:01.742 --> 04:03.744
Oh, I still don't know
what it is.

04:03.777 --> 04:05.713
But I know
what I wish it was...

04:05.746 --> 04:07.615
[ "Was" echoing ]

04:07.648 --> 04:09.317
Whoo!

04:09.350 --> 04:10.351
We're rich!

04:10.384 --> 04:11.752
[ Laughter, cheering ]

04:11.785 --> 04:14.388
We never have to worry about
the end of the month again!

04:14.422 --> 04:16.424
I could get a submarine
to school every day!

04:16.457 --> 04:18.158
But there's no water
between here and school.

04:18.191 --> 04:20.060
We'll buy some.
Exactly!

04:20.093 --> 04:23.897
I can finally call myself
"retired" instead of unemployed!

04:23.931 --> 04:25.433
Come on, let's go.

04:25.466 --> 04:27.234
Anais: Mom,
where are you taking us?

04:27.267 --> 04:28.469
You see,
such a large amount of cash

04:28.502 --> 04:29.803
is bound to belong
to somebody shady,

04:29.837 --> 04:31.705
and it's very likely
that...

04:31.739 --> 04:34.508
[ Tires squeal, all scream ]
...they'll send someone
to retrieve it.

04:34.542 --> 04:36.176
[ Espionage music plays ]

04:36.209 --> 04:38.579
Wait! So now we're on the run
from a hit man?!

04:38.612 --> 04:39.647
Exactly.

04:39.680 --> 04:41.415
[ Tires squealing ]

04:41.449 --> 04:42.716
[ Engine revs ]

04:42.750 --> 04:46.253
[ Alarm clanging ]

04:48.055 --> 04:50.624
[ All screaming ]

04:50.658 --> 04:53.794
[ Train whistle blows ]

04:53.827 --> 04:55.629
[ Knuckles crack ]

04:55.663 --> 04:58.198
Darwin: So now we have to live
every day like it's our last?!

04:58.231 --> 05:01.435
Yes. But isn't that
a good philosophy to have?

05:01.469 --> 05:02.403
Carpe diem!

05:02.436 --> 05:04.872
[ Screams ]
Gumball: Run!

05:05.839 --> 05:07.508
[ Wind howls ]

05:07.541 --> 05:09.309
[ All panting ]

05:11.412 --> 05:12.846
[ Radar chirping ]

05:12.880 --> 05:14.114
[ Beep ]

05:14.147 --> 05:15.916
I think I know
how he's tracking us.

05:15.949 --> 05:17.518
I'm sorry.
I'm just so scared.

05:17.551 --> 05:19.119
What the?!
Not that!

05:19.152 --> 05:20.921
There must be some kind of
tracking device in the money.

05:20.954 --> 05:22.856
[ All scream ]

05:24.958 --> 05:27.595
[ Beeping ]

05:27.628 --> 05:29.630
[ Engine revs ]

05:29.663 --> 05:31.865
[ Explosion ]

05:31.899 --> 05:33.066
Henchman: Huh.

05:33.100 --> 05:35.035
My employers
will never give up.

05:35.068 --> 05:37.104
There will be
another man after me,

05:37.137 --> 05:39.072
then another,
and another after that.

05:39.106 --> 05:41.108
You will never find peace.

05:41.141 --> 05:43.310
Yes,
but we're millionaires.

05:43.343 --> 05:45.546
You'll never get back
to your old life.

05:45.579 --> 05:47.080
You'll be hunted.

05:47.114 --> 05:48.416
Hunted millionaires.

05:48.449 --> 05:50.918
You will never be able
to trust anyone.

05:50.951 --> 05:52.586
You'll be fugitives.

05:52.620 --> 05:54.354
Fugitive millionaires.

05:54.388 --> 05:55.956
I agree with Mom
on one thing --

05:55.989 --> 05:58.125
what's inside this box
is clearly evil.

05:58.158 --> 05:59.192
What?
Why?

05:59.226 --> 06:00.594
Because history
has proven

06:00.628 --> 06:03.497
that mysterious containers
always bring misery --

06:03.531 --> 06:04.698
Pandora's Box?

06:04.732 --> 06:06.600
[ Gothic choir singing ]

06:06.634 --> 06:07.835
The Lost Ark?

06:07.868 --> 06:09.503
[ Epic music plays ]

06:09.537 --> 06:12.205
That six-month-old takeout box
at the back of the fridge?

06:12.239 --> 06:13.841
[ Demonic scream ]

06:13.874 --> 06:17.678
My point is, what if this box
was never meant to be opened?

06:17.711 --> 06:18.712
What if it was...

06:18.746 --> 06:20.180
[ Groaning ]

06:20.213 --> 06:21.982
It's been seven weeks
since the infection began,

06:22.015 --> 06:23.350
and I still haven't
found a cure.

06:23.383 --> 06:24.952
They've taken over everything.

06:24.985 --> 06:26.319
[ Sirens wailing in distance ]

06:26.353 --> 06:27.788
Our infrastructure
has collapsed,

06:27.821 --> 06:29.156
the people are on their own.

06:29.189 --> 06:31.158
Hello! You have reached
the mailbox of

06:31.191 --> 06:33.060
[zombie groaning]
Police Station.

06:33.093 --> 06:34.662
All our officers are busy

06:34.695 --> 06:36.430
consuming the flesh
of the living at the moment,

06:36.464 --> 06:39.600
so please take the law
into your own hands.

06:39.633 --> 06:41.635
[ Screaming ]

06:41.669 --> 06:43.403
Oh, wait up.

06:43.437 --> 06:45.839
Ah, cool.
[ Screams ]

06:45.873 --> 06:47.775
Scientist:
Most of the population
is now contaminated.

06:47.808 --> 06:51.144
Those that haven't transformed
yet were already zombies anyway.

06:52.179 --> 06:53.914
[ Whimpering ]

06:53.947 --> 06:55.749
[ Groaning ]

06:55.783 --> 06:58.185
[ Screams ]
Huh?

07:00.187 --> 07:02.355
[ Water running ]

07:02.389 --> 07:03.724
[ Gasps ]

07:03.757 --> 07:05.425
[ Laughs ]
[ Screams ]

07:05.459 --> 07:07.060
Scientist:
The world as we know it
is coming to an end.

07:07.094 --> 07:09.196
[ Growling ]
Get off, get off,
get off!

07:09.229 --> 07:10.598
Get off, get off,
get off!

07:10.631 --> 07:12.399
If only I had known
how the virus got out,

07:12.432 --> 07:14.301
maybe the infection
could have been prevented.

07:14.334 --> 07:18.171
[ Groaning intensifies ]
How did it all sta-a-art?!

07:20.240 --> 07:23.911
Ooh!
Squirt gun!

07:23.944 --> 07:25.946
[ Jazz cue plays ]

07:25.979 --> 07:28.381
We have to destroy
that box.

07:28.415 --> 07:30.751
I'm sure it's something
perfectly normal.

07:30.784 --> 07:32.019
Exactly.

07:32.052 --> 07:33.386
Like an accordion
made out of bread

07:33.420 --> 07:34.822
or a remote-controlled
trumpet.

07:34.855 --> 07:36.123
Uh, what?

07:36.156 --> 07:38.992
[ Quixotic music plays ]

07:40.160 --> 07:42.696
[ Cellphone rings, vibrates ]
[ Gasps ]

07:42.730 --> 07:44.364
Yes?

07:44.397 --> 07:47.501
Man:
[ Through cellphone, echoing ]
Lazarus.

07:47.535 --> 07:50.237
Our scientists have
inserted an implant
allowing you to use

07:50.270 --> 07:52.840
the capacities of your brain
at 100%,

07:52.873 --> 07:54.241
making you
the ultimate weapon.

07:54.274 --> 07:55.509
We will now
erase your memory

07:55.543 --> 07:57.277
and place you
under a false identity

07:57.310 --> 07:58.912
until it is time
for your mission.

07:58.946 --> 07:59.980
Your activation code word

08:00.013 --> 08:02.315
is [echoing] Lazarus.

08:02.349 --> 08:03.617
[ Through cellphone ]
Your mission

08:03.651 --> 08:05.218
is to save the president.
Please hang up.

08:05.252 --> 08:07.588
This phone will self-destruct
in 10 seconds.

08:08.589 --> 08:11.191
[ Timer beeping ]

08:13.060 --> 08:15.228
[ Tires squeal ]

08:18.799 --> 08:22.570
[ Timer beeping faster ]

08:25.773 --> 08:28.576
Ooh!
[ Grunting ]

08:33.113 --> 08:34.314
[ Whimpering ]

08:34.347 --> 08:36.116
Mr. President,
are you okay?

08:36.149 --> 08:37.551
I was so scared.

08:37.585 --> 08:40.621
Don't worry.
You're safe now.

08:40.654 --> 08:43.290
[ Dreamy music plays ]

08:46.894 --> 08:48.461
Uh, hang on.
No offense, Dad.

08:48.495 --> 08:50.063
It sounds cool
that you could use

08:50.097 --> 08:51.398
the full power
of your brain,

08:51.431 --> 08:53.100
but 100% of nothing
is still nothing.

08:53.133 --> 08:54.635
Man: [ Through cellphone ]
Please hang up.

08:54.668 --> 08:56.436
This phone will self-destruct
in 10 seconds.

08:56.469 --> 08:58.205
No, you hang up.
[ Timer beeping ]

08:58.238 --> 08:59.539
I'm serious.
Please hang up.

08:59.573 --> 09:01.274
[ Giggles ]
No, you first.

09:01.308 --> 09:03.443
This is a direct order.
Please hang up!

09:03.476 --> 09:05.879
All right,
we'll do it at the same time.

09:05.913 --> 09:08.548
One...two --

09:08.582 --> 09:12.119
[ Screaming ]

09:12.152 --> 09:13.520
[ Grunts ]

09:13.553 --> 09:14.554
[ Growls ]

09:14.588 --> 09:16.123
Oh.

09:16.156 --> 09:17.157
[ Gasps ] Stop!

09:17.190 --> 09:18.191
[ Smooching ]
Mwah!

09:18.225 --> 09:20.193
Oh!
[ Whimpers ]

09:20.227 --> 09:21.461
No, where's...?

09:21.494 --> 09:23.263
Ahem.

09:23.296 --> 09:25.498
We need to get this box
back to the right person!

09:25.532 --> 09:27.835
The president has to be saved --
and kissed!

09:27.868 --> 09:29.436
What if it was just a box?

09:29.469 --> 09:30.638
That would be
a huge letdown.

09:30.671 --> 09:32.606
Think about it --
a cardboard box

09:32.640 --> 09:35.142
could be a spaceship,
a time machine,

09:35.175 --> 09:38.478
♪ A pirate boat
fighting a giant squid ♪

09:38.511 --> 09:41.715
♪ If you look at it
through the eyes of a kid ♪

09:41.749 --> 09:43.717
I said it would be
a huge letdown!

09:43.751 --> 09:46.987
I don't care what's inside it.
I just want the box.

09:47.020 --> 09:48.455
We need to destroy it.
No!

09:48.488 --> 09:50.123
I saw it first!
It's mine!

09:50.157 --> 09:52.392
[ All shouting indistinctly ]

09:56.596 --> 09:58.832
[ All gasp ]

09:58.866 --> 10:00.433
[ All sigh ]

10:00.467 --> 10:02.302
[ All gasp, sigh ]

10:02.335 --> 10:03.336
[ Horn honking ]

10:03.370 --> 10:05.305
[ Gasping, sighing continues ]

10:05.338 --> 10:06.874
[ Horn honking ]

10:13.113 --> 10:15.115
[ Doorbell rings ]

10:15.148 --> 10:16.583
[ Gasps ]
My favorite.

10:16.616 --> 10:18.719
Have you guys received
a package, by any chance?

10:18.752 --> 10:20.921
I told them to leave it here
if I wasn't home.

10:20.954 --> 10:22.555
[ All gasp ]

10:22.589 --> 10:24.557
Oh, uh,
I don't think so.

10:24.591 --> 10:26.326
Eh, never mind.
Wait!

10:26.359 --> 10:28.261
Maybe we opened it
by mistake.

10:28.295 --> 10:29.296
What was inside?

10:29.329 --> 10:30.363
You don't want to know.

10:30.397 --> 10:31.899
Trust me, we really do.

10:31.932 --> 10:34.301
Okay. You know that rough skin
you have on your elbow?

10:34.334 --> 10:36.036
Well, imagine that,
but a bit scalier

10:36.069 --> 10:37.537
and spreading
over your entire

10:37.570 --> 10:39.506
[groans] place
that should be soft.

10:39.539 --> 10:43.043
Now, imagine if that
skin also got marinated
in vinegar and microwaved,

10:43.076 --> 10:45.779
and hair somehow got trapped
under a layer of that skin

10:45.813 --> 10:48.215
and the hair kept growing
under this kind of blister

10:48.248 --> 10:50.751
that sort of also filled with
some butter-colored oily matter,

10:50.784 --> 10:52.285
and then it started
sweating --

10:52.319 --> 10:54.321
kind of like cheese,
but on live meat --

10:54.354 --> 10:56.589
until it hardened
into a flaking crust.

10:57.624 --> 10:59.760
Well, the box had some cream
in it for that.

10:59.793 --> 11:01.594
You're right.
We didn't want to know.

11:03.396 --> 11:07.434
♪♪
